Greyhound Corp said it hassigned a definitive agreement to buy General Motors Corp's U.S.Transit Bus and Parts business for an undisclosed sum.    The agreement, tentatively set in January, includesproduction tooling, design and equipment for urban transitbuses, inventories and trademark identification.    The agreement also incudes the right to buy GM's CanadianTransit Bus and Parts business, contingent on a satisfactorylabor agreement.    Greyhound said it will relocate the production facilities,currently in Pontiac, Michigan, to an undetermined location. Reuter&#3;